        <tocItem href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ssi/2017/72/code-of-practice/1/paragraph/3" level="2"><inline name="tocHeading">3. Introduction</inline></tocItem>
        <tocItem href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ssi/2017/72/code-of-practice/1/paragraph/4" level="2"><inline name="tocHeading">4. Primary Purposes of Stop and Search</inline></tocItem>
        <tocItem href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ssi/2017/72/code-of-practice/1/paragraph/5" level="2"><inline name="tocHeading">5. Securing public confidence and promoting community relations</inline></tocItem>
        <tocItem href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ssi/2017/72/code-of-practice/1/paragraph/6" level="2"><inline name="tocHeading">6. Part 2 When powers of Stop and Search may be used</inline></tocItem>
        <tocItem href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ssi/2017/72/code-of-practice/1/paragraph/7" level="2"><inline name="tocHeading">7. Personal factors alone can never support reasonable grounds for suspicion</inline></tocItem>
        <tocItem href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ssi/2017/72/code-of-practice/1/paragraph/8" level="2"><inline name="tocHeading">8. Reasonable grounds for suspicion based on information and/or intelligence</inline></tocItem>
        <tocItem href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ssi/2017/72/code-of-practice/1/paragraph/9" level="2"><inline name="tocHeading">9. Reasonable grounds for suspicion and searching groups</inline></tocItem>
        <tocItem href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ssi/2017/72/code-of-practice/1/paragraph/10" level="2"><inline name="tocHeading">10. Reasonable grounds for suspicion based on behaviour, time and location</inline></tocItem>
        <tocItem href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ssi/2017/72/code-of-practice/1/paragraph/11" level="2"><inline name="tocHeading">11. Questioning to decide whether to carry out a search</inline></tocItem>
        <tocItem href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ssi/2017/72/code-of-practice/1/paragraph/12" level="2"><inline name="tocHeading">12. Searches of persons not suspected of an offence</inline></tocItem>
        <tocItem href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ssi/2017/72/code-of-practice/1/paragraph/13" level="2"><inline name="tocHeading">13. Searches authorised under section 60 of the Criminal Justice and Public Order Act 1994</inline></tocItem>
        <tocItem href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ssi/2017/72/code-of-practice/1/paragraph/14" level="2"><inline name="tocHeading">14. Powers to search persons in the exercise of a power to search premises</inline></tocItem>
        <tocItem href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ssi/2017/72/code-of-practice/1/paragraph/15" level="2"><inline name="tocHeading">15. Part 3 – Engagement prior to a search</inline></tocItem>
        <tocItem href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ssi/2017/72/code-of-practice/1/paragraph/16" level="2"><inline name="tocHeading">16. Part 4 – How Stop and Search powers are to be used, recorded and monitored</inline></tocItem>
        <tocItem href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ssi/2017/72/code-of-practice/1/paragraph/17" level="2"><inline name="tocHeading">17. Steps to be taken prior to a search</inline></tocItem>
